race.comment: GLOWING RAPIDS (13) rewarded for his consistency when displayed good early toe for a dominant victory over 1100m at Bathurst. Drops sharply in weight in a very average BM66. Hard to catch again. LINE OF LAW (6) went fast early from the outside draw to score her fourth straight win over 1200m at Warren. Poorly drawn here and has solid claims if she can get some cheap sectionals midrace. DAO SUN (10) not that far away at his last two outings and drops 4.5kg for this. Strong through the line when fourth over 1000m at Quirindi when anchored with the 60.5kg. Will be charging at the business end. VIOLET AND BLUE (1) returns from a let-up. Will appreciate the claim again after holding on to finish a gritty second over 1000m at Queanbeyan in this grade. Well drawn and sure to be thereabouts.
